[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Is there a difference in the structure of banks in [bold]Northern [bold]Ireland[bold], compared to their structure in [bold]Great Britain[bold]? Is there any disadvantage for customers, both private and business, in NI as a result?[bold] [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]1.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Santander
[normal] does not differentiate its business in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal] compared to 
[normal]Great Britain
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We offer the same 
[normal]range of products to our customers and make lending decisions for both our individual customers 
[normal]and business customers 
[normal]in the same way. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]As a consequence of this, we do not believe that our customers are in any way disadvantaged by banking with 
[normal]Santander
[normal] in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal] as opposed to those banking with us in 
[normal]Great Britain
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Do banks [bold]that[bold] operate in both GB and NI, [bold]eg[bold], Barclays and Santander, operate differently in NI than in the rest of the [bold]UK[bold]? Does this result in customers in NI being at a [bold]disadvantage compared to customers in GB?[bold] [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]1.4.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]See 
[normal]above
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Historically, finance for start-ups and expansions had been largely provided through Government agencies – [bold]ie[bold], Invest NI &amp;[bold] its various predecessors – with the result that bank finance traditionally played a lesser [bold]role in NI than in GB.[bold] [bold]Have NI[bold] banks continued to play a lesser role in commercial finance than elsewhere – in particular, have economic and financial conditions s[bold]ince 2008 exacerbated that position? [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]2.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is 
[normal]Santander
[normal]’s
[normal] ambition to be the bank of choice for companies across the country
[normal], including
[normal] in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]While some of the banks
[normal] operating
[normal] in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal] have seen a declining appetite for lending si
[normal]nce 2008, 
[normal]Santander
[normal] 
[normal]is committed to
[normal] grow
[normal]ing this part of its business in the years ahead. O
[normal]ur experience over the last 18 months
[normal] suggests that
[normal] there is no shortage of SMEs seeking funding in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
