[normal]Santander
[normal] grew its ne
[normal]t lending to SMEs 
[normal]in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal] 
[normal]by 32% from a year earlier. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.4.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Funding for expansion for companies in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal], as in 
[normal]Great Britain
[normal], is often provided by banks in the form of invoice finance or factoring. These provide a 
[normal]high 
[normal]level of control and transparency, especially for younger businesses. These products are likely to remain popular for banks and businesses in the years ahead.
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.5.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Providing banking products for start up businesses is a challenge that banks face in both 
[normal]Gre
[normal]at Britain
[normal] and 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal]. Banks find it difficult to provide lending to new businesses due to a lack of track record and, usually, a lack of trading data on which to base risk assessments. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.6.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]UK 
[normal]Government has sought to overcome this problem thro
[normal]ugh the Start-Up Loans programme. 
[normal]Santander
[normal] supports this initiative and considers it an excellent
[normal] example of how g
[normal]overnment can help more start up businesses grow and create jobs. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.7.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Start-
[normal]Up Loans are available to business in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal]. 
