[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How is new lending recorded; how much ‘new’ lending recorded is actually made up of extensions or additions to existing loans; and what [bold]are banks actually doing compared t[bold]o what they are advertising? [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]4.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Santander
[normal] has only been operating as a corporate bank in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal] for the last 3 years. As most of our loan facilities last for a 5 year period, we have not yet had any 
[normal]customer facilities expire which need
[normal] renewing. 
[normal]Consequently, the vast majority of 
[normal]our 
[normal]lending recorded in 
[normal]Northern Ireland
[normal] is new lending. 
